---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
	title="SMS Terms and Conditions | Water Heater Replacement Company"
	description="SMS Terms and Conditions for the internal lead notification system used by Water Heater Replacement Company of Grand Rapids."
	robotsIndex={false}
	robotsFollow={false}
	showNavigation={false}
	showFooter={false}
>
	<main class="min-h-screen bg-white py-16 px-6">
		<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">

			<header class="mb-10 pb-8 border-b border-gray-200">
				<p class="text-xs font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-gray-400 mb-3">Internal Use Only</p>
				<h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-black tracking-tight text-gray-900 mb-3">SMS Terms and Conditions</h1>
				<p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: June 30, 2026</p>
			</header>

			<div class="space-y-10 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">

				<p>
					Please read these SMS Terms and Conditions carefully. By opting into our internal alert and notification
					system, you agree to be bound by these terms.
				</p>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">1. Program Description</h2>
					<p>
						This program is strictly used for internal operational alerts to notify authorized business owners,
						administrators, and designated internal staff members when a new customer lead form is submitted on our
						corporate website. This system is private, internal, and is never used to message external customers
						or for marketing purposes.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">2. Message Frequency</h2>
					<p>
						Message frequency varies based on site activity. You will receive an automated text
						notification only when an active lead form is submitted on our website.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">3. Cost and Carrier Fees</h2>
					<p>
                        We do not charge for this service. However, <strong>message and data rates may apply</strong> for any messages sent or received. Messages are only sent to company-provided devices, and any corporate carrier billing charges incurred will be covered by the company per internal policy.
                    </p>
                </section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">4. Opt-Out Instructions</h2>
					<p>
						You can cancel the SMS service at any time. Just text <strong>STOP</strong> to our phone number.
						After you send the SMS message <strong>STOP</strong> to us, we will send you an SMS message to confirm
						that you have been unsubscribed. After this, you will no longer receive SMS messages from us. To
						reactivate, contact your system administrator.
					</p>
                    <p class="mt-3">
                        <strong>Employment Disclaimer: </strong>While users may opt out of the SMS delivery mechanism at any time by texting STOP, receipt of lead alerts is a mandatory requirement of your employment role. Opting out of the SMS delivery mechanism requires you to immediately configure an alternative, approved alert mechanism (such as email) with your system administrator, or you may face internal disciplinary action per company policy.
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">5. Support and Help</h2>
					<p>
						If you are experiencing issues with the messaging program you can reply with the keyword <strong>HELP</strong>
						for more assistance, or you can get help directly by contacting your system administrator.
					</p>
				</section>

				<section>
					<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">6. Carrier Liability Disclaimer</h2>
					<p>
						<strong>Carriers are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.</strong> Delivery depends on
						effective transmission from your network operator.
					</p>
				</section>

			</div>

		</div>
	</main>
</BaseLayout>
